    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-01-13T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-01-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="766"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d766">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85322/1–1354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 766<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Syria (<persName corresp="#p_MJS1"
                            type="from">Moose</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d766fn1">Repeated to Beirut, Cairo, London, Tel Aviv, Paris,
                        Moscow, Baghdad, Amman, Jidda, and Jerusalem; passed to New York and to the
                        Department of Defense.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-01-13T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 13, 1954—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>275. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 271, January 12. Substance
                    paragraph 3 (a) <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 281, January 11,
                    conveyed to <persName corresp="#p_ASGA1">Shishakli</persName> during long
                    interview January 13. Syrian President made following points: (1) Government of
                    Syria desires <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> resolution on diversion project;
                    (2) sole Syrian aim is to protect its rights in Jordan waters and <persName
                        corresp="#p_ZDF1">Zeineddine</persName> suggestions drafted this aim in
                    view; (3) professed inability understand how US Government could approve text so
                    detrimental Syrian interests, emphasizing Government of Syria could not accept
                    less than explicit recognition rights; (4) if justice not obtainable, Syria
                    could as last resort rely upon Russian veto.</p>
                <p>I stated Department aware this possibility and emphasized views paragraph 3(b)
                        <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 281. <persName corresp="#p_ASGA1"
                        >Shishakli</persName> replied continued indifference tripartite powers would
                    leave him no choice but reluctantly accept Russian help. His attention was
                    called risks attendant cooperation with Soviets and danger Israeli resumption
                    work if no resolution passed. Syrian President declared he recognized risks and
                    emphasized Syria would use all its resources defend its rights in event work
                    resumed. Added “this time Syria will not be kicked.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MJS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
